content:
Storage S3 job &#34;aws&#34; &#34;s3&#34; { region = &#34;us-east-1&#34; config &#34;chaos&#34; { tag = &#34;PREFIX:second&#34; chaos = &#34;terminate&#34; count = 2 } } S3 uses PREFIX and SUFFIX to find specific buckets, if bucket name is &ldquo;db-files-inventory-qa&rdquo; you can find this bucket with &ldquo;PREFIX:db&rdquo; or &ldquo;inventory-qa&rdquo;
chaos config:
terminate: Finds specified S3 buckets, deletes the content and terminate the buckets. delete_content: Will delete N number ( with count parameter) of objects in specified buckets.
